<div id="pf2cbc" class="pf w47 h23c" data-page-no="2cbc"><div class="pc pc2cbc w47 h23c"><div class="t m2496 x27 h4 y2c9b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. What is the true relationship </div><div class="t m1223 xb9 h4 y2a73 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">between faith and works? James 2:20, </div><div class="t m1741 xb9 h4 y2ca3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22, 26. </div><div class="t mcd3 x15 h4 y23c5 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—&quot;Genuine faith will be manifested </div><div class="t me2f xb9 h4 yf11 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in good works; for good works are the </div><div class="t m60a xb9 h4 y20b1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fruits of faith. As God works in the heart, </div><div class="t mb17 xb9 h4 y18f9 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and man surrenders his will to God and co-</div><div class="t m338 xb9 h4 y1763 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">operates with God, he works out in the life </div><div class="t m155 xb9 h4 y1681 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">what God works in by the Holy Spirit, and </div><div class="t m6a7 xb9 h4 y1b41 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there is harmony between the purpose of </div><div class="t mf35 x3 h4 y1a63 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the heart and the practice of the life. . . . </div><div class="t m4db x3 h4 y1ef ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is an evidence that a man is not justified </div><div class="t m1b1 xb9 h4 y1720 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by faith when his works do not correspond </div><div class="t m203 xb9 h4 y1884 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to his profession. . . . The believer is justi-</div><div class="t m8c x3 h4 y1ca ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fied without any merit of his own. . . . He </div><div class="t m9b1 x3 h4 y199b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is justified through redemption that is in </div><div class="t m192 x3 h4 yc1a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ Jesus. . . . But while he is justified </div><div class="t md8 x3 h4 y197c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">because of the merit of Christ, he is not free  </div><div class="t m5e6 x58 h4 y2b14 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to work unrighteousness. Faith works by </div><div class="t m10c x58 h4 y2c3f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">love and purifies the soul. . . . Where faith </div><div class="t m30c x58 h4 y2c3e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is, good works appear. The sick are visited, </div><div class="t m41d x58 h4 y2bb8 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the poor are cared for, the fatherless and the </div><div class="t m228 x58 h4 y287e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">widows are not neglected, the naked are </div><div class="t m3eb x58 h4 y28e6 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">clothed, the destitute are fed. Christ went </div><div class="t md10 x58 h4 y23c1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">about doing good, and when men are united </div><div class="t m1168 x58 h4 y1b54 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with Him, they love the children of God, </div><div class="t m418 x58 h4 y1a0e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and meekness and truth guide their foot-</div><div class="t mc0 x58 h30 yb28 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">steps.&quot;—Selected Messages, </div><div class="t m494 xcc h4 yb29 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">b. 1, pp. 397, </div><div class="t m73b x58 h4 y1a58 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">398. </div><div class="t m8b x23 h71 yf8f ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Think on These Things </div><div class="t m1e3 x21 h71 y1b43 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Is </div><div class="t m9e5 xab h4 y1a63 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">it faith or presumption to demand that </div><div class="t mbd x58 h4 y1ef ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God fulfill certain promises as we under-</div><div class="t m9d8 x58 h4 y1720 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">stand them? </div><div class="t m7db x70 h4 y1884 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When we pray for greater faith, what may </div><div class="t m4e x58 h4 y1ca ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">we expect? </div><div class="t m188 x70 h4 y1885 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Am I developing faith, day by day, by </div><div class="t ma66 x1c h4 yc1a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trusting God for the lesser needs of every-</div><div class="t m398 x1c h4 y54 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 